1 exists for the primary purpose of dealing with employers concerning grievances, labor disputes, wages, rates of
2 pay, hours of employment, fringe benefits, or other conditions of employment.
3
4 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Freedom of choice guaranteed. An individual may not be required as a
5 condition of employment or continuation of employment to:
6 (1) resign or refrain from voluntary membership in, voluntary affiliation with, or voluntary financial
7 support of a labor organization;
8 (2) become or remain a member of a labor organization or pay dues, fees, assessments, or other
9 charges of any kind or amount to a labor organization; or
10 (3) pay a charity or other third party, in lieu of payment to a labor organization, an amount
11 equivalent to or a pro rata portion of dues, fees, assessments, or other charges of any kind regularly required of
12 members of a labor organization.
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Voluntary deductions protected. (1) It is unlawful for an employer to
15 deduct from the wages, earnings, or compensation of an employee any dues, fees, assessments, or other
16 charges of any kind to be held for, transferred to, or paid over to a labor organization unless the employee has
17 first presented, and the employer has received, a signed written authorization for the deductions.
18 (2) The authorization given pursuant to subsection (1) may be revoked by the employee by
19 submitting written notice to the employer at any time and that revocation must be effective 30 days after notice
20 is given.
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Agreements in violation and actions to induce agreements illegal.
23 (1) An agreement, understanding, or practice, written or oral, implied or expressed, between a labor
24 organization and an employer that violates the rights of an employee guaranteed by [sections 1 through 10] is
25 void.
26 (2) Any strike, picketing, boycott, or other action by a labor organization to induce or attempt to
27 induce an employer to enter into an agreement prohibited by [sections 1 through 10] is illegal and constitutes a
28 violation of [sections 1 through 10].
