2 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Posted notice required. An employer shall continuously display the
3 following notice in a place or places where it may be readily seen by all employees in the employer's business
4 establishment and shall furnish a copy of the notice to each employee when the employment begins and ends:
5 "EMPLOYEE FREEDOM OF CHOICE
6 Under the law of the state of Montana, an employee is protected in the exercise of the employee's
7 freedom of choice to join or to refrain from joining a labor organization. It is unlawful for a labor organization and
8 an employer to enter into a contract or agreement that requires the employee to pay dues, fees, assessments,
9 or other charges of any kind to a labor organization as a condition of obtaining or retaining a job. Under this law,
10 an employer may not discharge or otherwise discriminate against an employee because of the employee's
11 refusal to join or pay dues, fees, assessments, or other charges of any kind to a labor organization."
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Criminal penalties. A violation of [sections 1 through 10] is a
14 misdemeanor, and on conviction, an individual, employer, or labor organization or an agent or representative of
15 an employer or labor organization shall be fined an amount of up to $1,000. A violation of [sections 1 through
16 10] is an absolute liability offense as provided in 45-2-104.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Civil penalties. A person harmed as a result of a violation or threatened
19 violation of [sections 1 through 10] may:
20 (1) file a complaint to enjoin the violator or person threatening violation; and
21 (2) recover damages, including costs and reasonable attorney fees, resulting from the violation or
22 threatened violation.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 10. Exceptions. [Sections 1 through 10] do not apply to:
25 (1) employers and employees to the extent that they are subject to the Railway Labor Act, 45
26 U.S.C. 151, et seq.;
27 (2) the United States or employees of the United States;
28 (3) employers and employees on exclusive federal enclaves; or
