3 Section 11. Section 39-31-201, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "39-31-201. Public employees protected in right of Right to self-organization -- choice as to
5 membership. (1) Public employees shall have and shall be protected in the exercise of the right of self-
6 organization, to form, join, or assist any labor organization, to bargain collectively through representatives of
7 their own choosing on questions of wages, hours, fringe benefits, and other conditions of employment, and to
8 engage in other concerted activities for the purpose of collective bargaining or other mutual aid or protection
9 free from interference, restraint, or coercion.
10 (2) A public employee, on an individual basis, has the right to choose not to join or assist any labor
11 organization, and to be free from interference, restraint, or coercion."
12
13 Section 12. Section 39-31-203, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "39-31-203. Deduction of dues from employee's pay. Upon On written authorization of any public
15 employee within a bargaining unit, the public employer shall deduct from the pay of the public employee the
16 monthly amount of dues as certified by the secretary of the exclusive representative and shall deliver the dues
17 to the treasurer of the exclusive representative.
18 (2) The authorization given pursuant to subsection (1) may be revoked by the public employee at
19 any time by submitting written notice to the public employer 30 days before the date of revocation. A public
20 employer receiving an authorization from a public employee shall promptly notify the employee in writing of the
21 employee's right to revoke the authorization by giving the employer 30 days' written notice."
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 13. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 10] are intended to be
24 codified as an integral part of Title 39, chapter 33, and the provisions of Title 39, chapter 33, apply to [sections
25 1 through 10].
26
